post_text:
Swan Valley School District Families,

You may have recently seen the following press release from the USDA:
https://bit.ly/2F3W3bD
Effective Tuesday (9/8), all children up to age 18 (including in person and remote learners and siblings under school age) now receive daily free breakfast and lunch. The USDA is extending nationwide waivers for the Summer Food Service Program. This continues until December 31, 2020 or "until funding runs out."

This is retroactive to the start of school. Meals that have already been purchased this school year will be credited back to a student's account.

As a reminder, Swan Valley Schools is offering curbside pick-up breakfast and lunch meals for all REMOTE students enrolled in our district. Pickup is Tuesday and Thursday from 11-1 and 4-6 at the main entrance of the High School. You must sign up for this meal service if you would like to be included.
For more information , visit the Swan Valley School District website under the Nutrition Services Department.
The form to sign up for curbside pickup is here: https://bit.ly/3gp8IDm

post_text: Swan Valley School District families,We are very much anticipating the start of the new school year in just over one week! Recent discussions with the Saginaw County Department of Public Health, the district administrative team, and the SVSD School Board have elicited a need to further clarify our viewpoint on facial coverings for elementary age students. While masks are still not required to be worn by elementary age students once in the classroom, it is strongly recommended that parents encourage their students to wear their masks at all times while in the building. Thank you in advance for your cooperation with this matter.

**Just a reminder for tonight's drive thru graduation**

Attention residents living near Swan Valley High School. There will be a drive thru graduation ceremony on July 27th starting at 6pm for the graduating class of 2020. To accommodate the many vehicles that may be participating, O'Hern Rd will be closed to thru traffic from Fritzler Dr to Van Wormer Rd starting at 5:30pm to the conclusion of the ceremony.
Traffic on Van Wormer Rd will be restricted to vehicles traveling south only on Van Wormer Rd from Crooked Creek Dr to Schomaker Rd. Please avoid the area during this time.

Heidi McGrandy Photography added 115 new photos to the album: Swan Valley Senior Cap and Gown Delivery! — at Swan Valley High School.
June 26 at 7:21 AM · Saginaw, MI ·

The staff of Swan Valley made Cap and Gown delivery very special!

The seniors were greeted by our own Police and Fire departments and our special Mom animal friends, they received SV bracelets upon entry and raced for a prize to find their caps and gowns!

There was also a dance off, corn hole game and photo booth for treats, but the most popular was the Pie in the Face to Mr. McRae!

So much fun was had and it was great to see you all again!! I look forward to seeing you in July for your graduation ceremony.

Stay tuned to Facebook and watch for another Cap and Gown Event from me!

text:
Outstanding interview, SV Valedictorian, Sam Lea: https://www.mlive.com/news/saginaw-bay-city/2020/06/hear-swan-valley-valedictorian-samuel-lea-deliver-his-online-commencement-speech.html

MLIVE.COM
Hear Swan Valley valedictorian Samuel Lea deliver his online commencement speech

post_text: June 1, 2020 was supposed to be your graduation date. Due to circumstances beyond everyone's imagination and control, that is not possible. Although this is not a replacement for a "normal commencement," we still wanted to join you in celebrating your graduation on your original date. We look forward to July 27, 2020 as we plan to host an in person event to truly recognize your high school graduation as conditions allow. There is an old adage "the best laid plans of mice and men often go astray" (attributed to poet Robert Burns) and there is no truer example of that statement than the current pandemic. We would like to acknowledge the volunteers of the Graduation Committee, Mrs. Lalejini for her outstanding work on producing this video tribute and Mrs. Mazany and Mr. LaBrake for their work over the last four years with the Class of 2020. Congratulations Swan Valley Seniors! Please enjoy the Class of 2020’s video recognition by clicking on the following link: https://bit.ly/SVHSGraduation

Today would have been Decision Day in the Library where all students stood up and said their future plans in front of all of their peers. We are disappointed that it didn’t turn out as planned, but we had a lot of fun putting together this video congratulating our seniors on what they’ve accomplished and what they plan to do in the future. Please watch and share in the fun and congratulate any seniors you know. They’ve worked hard this year and earned a celebration!

https://drive.google.com/open?id=1odhjxd4H-D2qyqrHJuuLUjaYmBD0DrXA

Dear Class of 2020 Parents:
We are working on a collage of memories for the Class of 2020 online graduation experience that will take place June 1st. Here is where you come in: please submit ONE photo of your child (in a group, etc) at a school event, sporting event, etc from elementary, middle, or high school. You pick the era! (Please label with your child's name and the era.) Photos are due Tuesday, May 26 to ensure Mrs. Lalejini can complete the video in time.
Please email your photo to Mrs. Lalejini: alalejini@swanvalley.k12.mi.us
subject line: MEMORY PHOTO (so it doesn't get lost in the shuffle!)
Thank you,
SVHS Staff

If you have already thanked or shown your appreciation for a Swan Valley teacher this week, thank another teacher in the district you've had. Without our educators, our students would only be ATHLETES missing those skills and attributes acquired in the classroom to be successful in the future. VIKING PRIDE!

Swan Valley High School
April 14 at 4:53 PM ·

#VikingPrideLights

This Friday night, April 17th, Swan Valley High School and Athletic Department will honor its seniors and senior athletes by turning the Football Field lights on at 8:20 p.m. The lights will be turned on at 20:20 military time for 20 minutes and 20 seconds to represent the Class of 2020. All Swan Valley School District families and community members are encouraged to safely participate in this event by staying home and turning on their porch and flood lights at this time. Every attempt will be made to livestream the Football Field on the Swan Valley Athletics Facebook page for those families living out of district.

Although this does not do justice in recognizing our Viking Seniors for their years of blood, sweat, and tears, this is the least we can do to honor a brave and amazing class.

Join in by taking a picture of your lights and tagging #VikingPrideLights

Friday's SV Athletic Department Social Engagement Activity:

Today marks 4 full weeks since we have been able to be in-session within our buildings. Athletes, take this day to make sure you are ready for Monday's "Learning from Home" by checking in with your teachers and Schoology. Coaches and parents, help provide support as our students transition into a completely new and unfamiliar world of remote learning. It can’t replace face-to-face instruction, but let’s make this last 25% of the school year as successful as possible. Viking Pride!

Rotary of Saginaw Valley
February 24 at 3:07 PM ·

We are excited to announce that Adlar Feldotte and Sam Lea have each earned Rotary Scholarships in the amount of $1,000! Swan Valley High School can be proud of these two community leaders! Adlar and Sam were participants in Rotary Youth Leadership Camp last summer. They also spend time tutoring younger students, lead charitable causes at school and are involved with Business Professionals of America among several other worthy causes. Adlar is headed to SVSU and Sam has narrowed down his options to Wayne State and Central Michigan. Both plan to continue their education in STEM.
Come see Adlar, Sam and our other young leaders as we honor them at this year’s Rotary Fundraiser, May 14th at the Saginaw Children’s Zoo!
#serviceaboveself

Swan Valley Athletics
February 22 at 9:41 PM ·

Weekend Results for Swan Valley Sports:
-Congrats to grapplers Cody and Tyler Ueberroth for qualifying for the state wrestling tournament today!
-Kudos to the Tri-Valley Titans for winning their last regular season game against Midland High last night 6-4!
-The Boys Bowlers placed 7th and the Girls 4th in the TVC Conference Tournament at Northern Lanes in Sanford. Individually, Abby Bremer earned 1st Team All Conference, Elizabeth Simon and Zack Mitchell 2nd Team, and Brayden Lemmer Honorable Mention.
-The Cheer Team fell just short of qualifying for Regionals at Bullock Creek with a 5th place finish and a score of 656. Much improved ladies!
